Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.20,0:18:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,believer\Nas a child and as I grew up, when I saw
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.96,0:18:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the complete suffering, the totality of\Nthe suffering of mankind, I became an
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.36,0:18:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,atheist. And I became just as devout an\Natheist as I had been a theist.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.44,0:18:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And it took me some decades to transcend\Nthat
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.32,0:18:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,uh transition.\NGod is not within the province of the
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.44,0:18:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,provable or the intellect. Therefore,\Natheism
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.40,0:18:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and theism are both foolish.\NPlay play with the intellect. You can
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.60,0:18:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,neither prove God nor disprove God. God\Nis the source and essence of the
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.12,0:19:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,subjective state of\Ncalled enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.20,0:19:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The sense of iness\Nis autonomous. There is no entity or
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.24,0:19:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,person that experiences\None's existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.28,0:19:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,One existence is all that is. There is\Nno duality between a me or an I
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.40,0:19:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and consciousness.\NAnd that is called the state of
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.00,0:19:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,enlightenment.\NThe realization that that which you are
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.44,0:19:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,is all there is. That you are it.\NWhatever there is is what you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.00,0:19:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,God is the radical subjectivity\Nof and that's called selfreization.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.72,0:19:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The realization of the divinity of the\Nessence of your own existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.76,0:20:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,that nothing exists other than God.\NThere's nothing that exists outside of
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.40,0:20:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,divinity.\NAll that exists is divinity in its
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.20,0:20:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,various forms,\Nincluding atheism.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.84,0:20:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The only thing that's cap capable of\Natheism is God.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.60,0:20:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,To be an atheist, you have to have\Nconsciousness. is to have consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.79,0:20:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to have the presence of\Ndivinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.91,0:20:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Without God, you can't be an atheist.\NSo, thank God I'm an atheist. You can
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.88,0:20:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,say to yourself, "Thank you, God, that\NI'm an atheist. I don't have to go to
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.40,0:20:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,church and go to confession and do all\Nthat stuff." You know what I mean? I can
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.96,0:20:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,even meet on Fridays and\Nuse bad language.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.48,0:20:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Yep. God says, "Yep. Whatever you want\Nto be, baby, it's you."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.36,0:20:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,However, don't forget the little story\Nabout karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.84,0:21:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't forget the little karma blanket\Nthat you took yourself in bed with a
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.28,0:21:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,karma blanket.\NGod is in
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.96,0:21:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,descriptively\Nimminent and at the same time
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.67,0:21:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,transcendent\Nis all that is and is is all that is
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.15,0:21:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,not. The human experience of the\Npresence of God is the same in all ages
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.84,0:21:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and cultures\Nand all localities. The expressions of
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.03,0:21:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the awareness of presence of God\Nis is
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.03,0:21:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,part of all cultures throughout all of\Ntime.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.76,0:21:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Universality man intuitits it.\NIf you live on a deserted island in the
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.44,0:21:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,middle of nowhere,\Nthey have a belief in a holy spirit or
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.76,0:22:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,in an animal spirit or in the clouds or\Nthe sun or the sky. But every culture
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.52,0:22:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,includes divinity in one or another\Ndescription or form. Yes. And I've
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.55,0:22:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,visited the various cultures I've\Nvisited. God was encountered in each and
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.44,0:22:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,every one of them. Yes.\NAll right. God is descriptively
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.28,0:22:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,imminent as well as transcendent.\NThe human experience of the presence of
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.12,0:22:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,God is the same in all cultures, all\Nages
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.76,0:22:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and all localities.\NAnd if you study anthropology and all
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.72,0:22:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,the history of all the cultures of the\Nworld, you find that divinity exists in
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.08,0:22:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,various forms in every culture. Every\Nculture has a name for it. Name for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.84,0:22:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And they also have a name for that\Nentity for a person who doesn't believe
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.88,0:23:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,in it. And they they become outcasts.\NOutcasts.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.79,0:23:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Outcasts. Okay. Right. The effect of\Nhuman consciousness on the experience of
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.24,0:23:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the presence of God is subjectively\Ntransformative
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.00,0:23:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and identical throughout all of human\Nhistory.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.79,0:23:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You're sitting on the edge of a\Na cliff. You look out and suddenly
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.00,0:23:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a transformation of the entire\Nworld.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.40,0:23:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Transformation.\NRemember one time you're walking down
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.32,0:23:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the side of a hill in your home and\Nsuddenly
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.76,0:23:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,the world lit up with the presence.\N>> Can you tell them what that was like?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.60,0:23:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The beauty of it.\N>> I don't have a mic.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.48,0:23:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Oh, you don't have a mic. Mic?\N>> No. She told me she was just walking
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.88,0:24:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,along, not thinking about anything.\NAnd suddenly the overwhelming stunning
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.64,0:24:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,beauty of all of existence hit her like\Na huge uh thunder of beauty and light.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.12,0:24:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's like you see what you've always\Nseen but at much greater depth. What you
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.76,0:24:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,see is the div not only what exists but\Nthe divinity of all that exists. You now
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.15,0:24:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,have how many people here have had that\Nexperience? You suddenly see the
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.96,0:24:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,divinity of that which exists. Huh?\NIt leaves a timeless mark that is
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.20,0:24:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,available as a cali as a calibration\Nof a recorded level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.52,0:24:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, right. See, let's see. All right. So\Nthe calibration we can calibrate the
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.96,0:25:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,level of consciousness.\NUh shall we do that of that vision?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.24,0:25:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Mhm.\N>> Yes, we'll do it of that vision. What's
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.20,0:25:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,over 600,\N700,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.79,0:25:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,680,\N690, 690. It's a beautiful level of
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.84,0:25:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness\Nuh enlightened level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.15,0:25:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So suddenly the world lit up\Nand was transformed
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.84,0:25:26.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and what you became aware of was the\Nstunning beauty. The incredible beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.79,0:25:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Everything was 3D.\N>> Everything was 3D.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.64,0:25:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything was three-dimensional. Wow.\NMhm.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.12,0:25:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So how many people have had\Ntransformative experiences like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.52,0:25:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. A number of people. Thank God. Uh\Nwe thank God for that for for that gift.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.67,0:25:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how we call enlightenment a gift.\NIt's not something that you've earned
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.00,0:25:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and acquired or paid for etc. It's like\Na gift from divinity. Suddenly you're
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.27,0:26:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,walking along the street and the street\Nlights up and you see the miraculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.08,0:26:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the miraculous.\NThe essence of God does not include
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.36,0:26:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,human frailties\Nsuch as partiality.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.96,0:26:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It's beyond the desire to control,\Nbeyond favoritism, beyond duality,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.48,0:26:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,beyond judgmentalism,\Nbeyond wrath,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.67,0:26:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,righteousness,\Nrighteous anger.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.36,0:26:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It's beyond resentment, limitation.\NIt's beyond vanity. It's beyond revenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.20,0:26:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It's beyond jealousy. It's beyond\Nretaliation.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.52,0:26:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It is beyond locality.\NSo consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.36,0:26:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes what you become. You become\Naware that what you are is consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.12,0:27:03.91,Default,,0,0,0,,itself.\NNot the content of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.91,0:27:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,but consciousness itself.\NIt isn't this body. It's the capacity to
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.08,0:27:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,comprehend the existence of this body.\NSo you can
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.72,0:27:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,exist in different realms\Nwithout a body.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.76,0:27:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,That is true.\NYou can exist without a body.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.88,0:27:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Well,\Nthe older you get, the less you need a
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.91,0:27:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,body, right? What good is it?\NWell, you know, it loves to eat dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.60,0:27:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Loves ice cream.\NSo, we hang around for a few reasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.00,0:27:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the favorite ice cream right\Ncurrently?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.20,0:28:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, you like coffee.\N>> Oh, coffee ice cream is our favorite.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.20,0:28:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Anyway, as you see, that's\Nimpersonal. Uh, it it just has to do
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.88,0:28:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,with realizing the value of all that\Nexists and allowing yourself the
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.15,0:28:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,enjoyment and recognition of it. And so,\NI thank God for ice cream.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.91,0:28:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I thank God for ice cream. And I say,\N"Dear God, thank you for this wonderful
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.36,0:28:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,ice cream."\NAnd the voice says, "Good deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.88,0:28:44.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Then tomorrow you shall have some more.\NAs you can see, the variations in the
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.79,0:28:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,understanding, comprehension, and\Ndescription of of uh divinity
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.88,0:28:59.27,Default,,0,0,0,,are widespread, widespread depending on\Nculture, time, age. But every culture
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.27,0:29:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,has its own Holy Spirit. Sometimes\Nconsidered to be nature spirits, but
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.39,0:29:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,still of a spiritual nature.\NWhen it's when we need rain, I always
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.03,0:29:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,remind the nature spirits that it hasn't\Nrained for a month now.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.03,0:29:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Just in case God and the nature spirits\Nhadn't noticed.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.96,0:29:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I always remind the nature spirits\Nwhen you get home,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.32,0:29:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,it hasn't rained for a month around\Nhere. You know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.64,0:29:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So the nature spirits sort of nudged God\Nand sure enough within two weeks it
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.64,0:29:46.79,Default,,0,0,0,,always rained. You know I said thank you\Nnature spirits. All right. The
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.79,0:29:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,variations of the depictions of divinity\Nreflect the availability of human
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.20,0:30:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,perception and the projections of the\Nimpediments of the ego as
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.64,0:30:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,positionalities. Okay. So we transcend\Nall these limitations.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.24,0:30:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. The purity of the presence of\NGod is traditionally the essence
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.67,0:30:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,of the ineffable quality\Ncalled holiness
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.72,0:30:25.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and is the basis for the depiction of\Nthe sacred. That which is sacred.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.91,0:30:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is devoid of content\Nis the equivalent of innocence.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.76,0:30:47.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So in a elevated state of consciousness\Nyou see the beauty and worth and beauty
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.91,0:30:55.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and inspiration of all that exists.\NAnd I always give the example as you're
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.03,0:31:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,walking down the sidewalk, there's this\Nlittle bug walking along.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.24,0:31:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,That little bug is now famous, famous\Nlittle bug.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.64,0:31:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore,\Nthe enlightened person carefully
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.32,0:31:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,steps over the little bug and blesses it\Nby your concern.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.20,0:31:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We bless the little bug because we\Nrealize that it represents
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.44,0:31:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,the evolution of consciousness as life\Nitself.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.08,0:31:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So we value life in all of its\Nexpressions.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.15,0:31:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,We appreciate all of life.\NTo be appreciative of your own existence
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.08,0:31:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and the existence of all that is is in\Nitself
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.20,0:31:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,a c a short course on enlightenment.\NI am grateful to thee, oh Lord, for this
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.03,0:31:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,stage, for this audience,\Nfor this wonderful cane.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.12,0:32:00.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I am thankful for the beautiful flowers.\NI'm thankful for a box of Kleenex.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.79,0:32:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Just think primitive man didn't have\NKleenex.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.96,0:32:13.91,Default,,0,0,0,,He just sort of blew his nose on his\Nsleeve. You know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.91,0:32:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You know where buttons come from in the\Nmilitary
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.84,0:32:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,military uniform. You'll see there's\Nalways buttons. It's because in cold
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.91,0:32:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,weather the the soldiers who would all\Nbe going
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.20,0:32:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and the commander couldn't stand it.\NThey had buttons put on sleeves of
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.15,0:32:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody. So, you can't rub your nose\Non your sleeve because of all the
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.88,0:32:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,buttons.\NSo, now you know what those buttons are
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.32,0:32:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,for, huh? A couple of them right here.\NThank God for buttons on our sleeves
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.20,0:33:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and we'd all be a mess to look at.\NThe self is God imminent, shines forth
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.96,0:33:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,of its own accord.\NJust as the sun shines forth when the
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.72,0:33:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,clouds are removed.\NTherefore, you see enlightenment is a
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.67,0:33:25.51,Default,,0,0,0,,totally different thing than what you\Nthought. You thought enlightenment is a
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.51,0:33:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,goal that I will pursue.\NInstead, you see that it is what happens
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.24,0:33:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,when you remove the its barriers.\NYou don't have to do anything to become
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.51,0:33:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,enlightened except stop being\Nunenlightened.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.24,0:33:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,How?\NHow? Baby,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.51,0:34:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,you is what is already.\NI is. Yep. You is.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.72,0:34:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm what? I'm what? What is?\NYou're what is.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.24,0:34:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,If you didn't is, you wouldn't be saying\Nwhat is.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.15,0:34:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Something has to be there to question\Nwho am I? How did I get to be where I
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.56,0:34:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,am? And how do I get enlightened?\NStop being unenlightened. It's simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.00,0:34:36.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You all agree.\NEverybody promises they will stop being
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.87,0:34:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,unenlightened.\NStick by your agreement.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.07,0:34:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You're all that is.\NYou're all that there can be. You're all
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.28,0:34:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that there ever was.\NWow.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.72,0:35:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Mean I don't have to do anything? Nope.\NDon't have to go anywhere? Nope.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.24,0:35:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't have to read anything? Nope. Don't\Nhave to sit in yoga postures and go
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.11,0:35:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,weirdy breathing? Nope.\NIt's a realization.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.40,0:35:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how long it took\Nbefore it snapped. I was unenlightened.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.32,0:35:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,But since I snapped my finger, I become\Nenlightened.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.32,0:35:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you notice anything?\NNo, you didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.80,0:35:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You're just making it up\Ncuz you think it'll make me happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.72,0:35:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't make me happy if you become\Nenlightened.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.72,0:35:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't care less.\NYou want to be unenlightened?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.16,0:36:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,That's fine.\NIt's very enlightened to let it be all
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.11,0:36:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,right that you're not enlightened.\NIf it's okay with you that you're not
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.24,0:36:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,enlightened, you already are. Quit\Nworrying about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.24,0:36:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Why seek what is?\Nwhat is already is.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.32,0:36:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,No point chasing your tail.\NNo point chasing your tail.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.07,0:36:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I want everybody to relax and be totally\Ncomplete, satisfied, and happy with just
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.56,0:36:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,what you are this instant.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.76,0:36:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody\Nnot satisfied with who or what they are
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.07,0:36:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,at this moment?\NWho wishes to be thrashed?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.32,0:37:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Trashed\Nand thrown overboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.11,0:37:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Self-awareness shines forth of its own\Naccord
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.52,0:37:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,when the obstacles have been removed.\NSo you don't have to seek enlightenment
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.16,0:37:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,at all.\NStop seeking enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.96,0:37:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Give it up.\NForget it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.35,0:37:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that okay?\NAnybody disagree? Any
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.59,0:37:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,stupid idiot out there that wants to\Ndisagree with the great doctor here
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.96,0:38:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,who knows everything\Nthat was ever known
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.40,0:38:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,anywhere and everywhere in the whole\Nuniverse.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.52,0:38:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That's where I started for starters.\NThat's just starters, folks.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.32,0:38:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,To know all that's knowable, all that's\Never been known, all that could be
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.44,0:38:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,known.\NThat's enough to do before lunch. You
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.59,0:38:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,know what I mean?\NIn between a peanut butter sandwich
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.07,0:38:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and a root beer\Nis the whole universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.04,0:38:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,When you eat that peanut butter sandwich\Nand you wash it down with root beer,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.00,0:38:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,you've just experienced\Nall that can be experienced of the
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.16,0:39:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,wondrousness and goodness of\Nenlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.64,0:39:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,That makes it pretty easy, doesn't it?\NTherefore, I want you to realize
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.68,0:39:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,something.\NI'm getting tired out here.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.44,0:39:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,That what you want to happen is already\Nhappened.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.35,0:39:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And your only problem is that you\Nhaven't recognized that it already is.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.92,0:39:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's already happened.\NIt's not possible to exist and be
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.00,0:39:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,conscious without being enlightened.\Nto see that you are all that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.64,0:39:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing can exist other than that.\NYou are all there is. There is nothing
